due to severe confinement, lack of free exercise, and the restriction of natural behaviors, animals
			 used in circuses suffer and are prone to health, behavioral, and
			 psychological problems;

the use of collapsible, temporary facilities in traveling circuses increases the risk of escaping
			 exotic and non-domesticated animals seriously harming workers and the
			 public;

traveling circuses bring people dangerously close to exotic and non-domesticated animals by
			 displaying animals in inappropriate, uncontrolled areas that are not
			 suited for the exhibition of such animals;

